               <unittitle>Smith, Emily A., "Dr. Nathan Smith" manuscript</unittitle>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_743226fdac30f3e8f5993567a1eee93c">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Contains manuscript titled "Dr. Nathan Smith. The Story of the remarkable life and work of Nathan Smith, B.M., M.D. with his letters –- and a brief sketch of the life and professional work of his Son Dr. Nathan Ryno Smith and of his grandson Dr. Alan Penniman Smith. Pioneers from the dark ages to the dawn of the splendid era of modern medicine and surgery, 1787 to 1895." Also includes photographs and an original letter on Alan Penniman Smith. Dr. Fishbein believed these are materials that Emily Smith did not publish in her book <title>
                     <part>Life and Letters of Nathan Smith</part>
                  </title>. Given to Dr. Fishbein by the Medical and Chirurgical Faculty of Maryland.</p>
            </scopecontent>
